le","updated":1782548997530,"id":"rmVdP1He_UnoJ-U2sUiG_","x":-2592.2290403405505,"seed":610259030,"boundElements":[{"id":"uGkEP6pTuwjMtVLkr3bu4","type":"arrow"},{"id":"o8Yof5b7gtLeFC0oyyCsi","type":"arrow"},{"id":"IlwCHHryC7LZbULVvP-Bu","type":"arrow"},{"id":"M3k6QoOHgMrJbS9hMDWSM","type":"arrow"},{"id":"zTYb4wvfZVyAku7yeelhd","type":"arrow"},{"id":"-m1g5-xffh36Gi_Qy0A6L","type":"arrow"}],"y":5830.7561408834845,"opacity":100,"height":1169.5772450003017,"width":1778.4897700796719,"frameId":null,"strokeStyle":"solid","versionNonce":404416406},{"seed":1341085078,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"HeOz06LhadrutpfF2oaqy","strokeWidth":1,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":28,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1782548725190,"locked":false,"text":"Open Qns","version":320,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b4L","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Open Qns","height":35,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1232937430,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-2570.5709142164042,"angle":0,"y":5758.1101770595906,"width":128.35198974609375},{"seed":1622348938,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"e2SWbfiybAHXX_4eHXiRV","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":28,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1782548873461,"locked":false,"text":"Q If using redis as DB how would we persist Data ?\nA. We could use AOF(Append onfly file) which would persist data in case of Redis being a DB\n\nQ. How Kafka -> Consumer -> Ingest in ElasticSearch ?\nA. \nEach Consumer would  do soemthing of this sort:\nwhile True:\n    event = kafka.poll()\n    transform(event)\n    bulk_index_to_elasticsearch()\n","version":314,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b5J","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Q If using redis as DB how would we persist Data ?\nA. We could use AOF(Append onfly file) which would persist data in case of Redis being a DB\n\nQ. How Kafka -> Consumer -> Ingest in ElasticSearch ?\nA. \nEach Consumer would  do soemthing of this sort:\nwhile True:\n    event = kafka.poll()\n    transform(event)\n    bulk_index_to_elasticsearch()\n","height":385,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":75435082,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":null,"x":-2510.576166210893,"angle":0,"y":5912.870332325735,"width":1275.3997802734375},{"seed":1849829206,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"0PWBpb0ntV85yXCLA4aVk","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":28,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1782548987216,"locked":false,"text":"Q. Base62 Encoding\n\nBASE62 = \"0123456789abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ\"\n\ndef encode(num):\n    if num == 0:\n        return BASE62[0]\n\n    result = []\n\n    while num > 0:\n        num, rem = divmod(num, 62)\n        result.append(BASE62[rem])\n\n    return ''.join(reversed(result))","version":75,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b5P","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Q. Base62 Encoding\n\nBASE62 = \"0123456789abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ\"\n\ndef encode(num):\n    if num == 0:\n        return BASE62[0]\n\n    result = []\n\n    while num > 0:\n        num, rem = divmod(num, 62)\n        result.append(BASE62[rem])\n\n    return ''.join(reversed(result))","height":525,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1912850646,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":null,"x":-2518.3056029171244,"angle":0,"y":6390.4063544024757,"width":1219.008056640625}],"version":2,"files":{},"appState":{"shouldCacheIgnoreZoom":false,"exportScale":2,"defaultSidebarDockedPreference":false,"openMenu":null,"showWelcomeScreen":true,"currentItemStrok